Comments: Ban/measure is in effect in all subnational jurisdictions

Smoke-free legislation does not meet criteria for a complete ban in public transport, which is defined such that smoking is not allowed at any time in any indoor area under any circumstances. However, the interpretation of the law by the Federal Ministry of Health results in a smoking ban in public transport in practice.
The legislation does not allow designated smoking rooms except if the health authority allows them by administrative act. Until now, no such administrative act has been made.
Provision adopted but not implemented by 31 December 2014
However the Minister may allow a person to smoke in a non-smoking area.
